This project is for a wireless wind transmitter based on esp32

The esp32 transmits using espnow for minimal latency to a receiver (either dedicated ttgo or pypilot_mfd) on the same wireless channel.

To do OTA update, power the sensors inverted or held up side down (never occurs in normal use)

If powered normally and booted, and then inverted for 3 seconds the access point is created without code.

The access point can also be enabled later by sending an espnow message to turn it on, in this case with the wireless code.
If the code is forgotten it must be inverted to regain access.



Normally it outputs wind direction, cup rotation period (in ms) and accelerometer data.   The conversion to wind speed and direction is done by the receiver.
